<Base
  title="Privacy | Resting Places"
  description="What Resting Places collects (very little), how the newsletter works, and the site's public-figures-only policy for interment records."
>
  <h1>Privacy</h1>
  <p class="lede">This site is static pages. It runs no analytics scripts, sets no cookies, and shows no ads at present.</p>

  <h2>The newsletter</h2>
  <p>
    If you subscribe to the newsletter, we store the email address you give us and use it for that newsletter only.
    Every email includes a working unsubscribe link, and unsubscribing removes your address. We do not sell, share,
    or enrich subscriber data. If no signup form is visible on the site, no capture service is active and no email
    data is being collected.
  </p>

  <h2>People named on this site</h2>
  <p>
    Interment records cover notable public figures only, defined by three tests applied together: the person has a
    Wikipedia article, a recorded death date, and a documented place of burial in Wikidata's public records. We do not
    publish records of private individuals, and we do not accept user submissions of burial information. If you believe
    a record is wrong, the source is the linked Wikidata item; corrections there flow into this site at the next build.
  </p>

  <h2>Third parties</h2>
  <p>
    Photographs are loaded from Wikimedia Commons servers, which see standard image requests. Outbound links to
    Wikipedia, Wikidata, OpenStreetMap, Google Maps, Find a Grave, and affiliate partners are plain links; nothing is
    sent to those sites unless you click them.
  </p>
</Base>
